        <back>
            <div>
                <note type="ref" xml:id="note_zh_1">This part of the inscription is badly damaged.
                    Even the number of characters actually carved is not clear. Our project team
                    tried to make some suggestion of what characters might have been carved.
                    However, it is not clear what sense the phrase 手成戌百佊 could make. Zhang2
                    transcribes 彼. Though 彼 can be written as 佊, but 佊 is a word on his own and
                    means "evil". Hence 百佊 as such could mean the evils.</note>
                <note type="display" xml:id="note_en_1">According to <ref target="ZhangZong2003">Zhang Zong 2003, 14</ref>, these seven Buddhas King of Great Emptiness
                    relate to the inscriptions in situ at Hongdingshan and to inscriptions in other
                    places in Dongping county.</note>
            </div>
        </back>
